<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but leaves 7-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-17 cm, elliptic-rhomboid, base truncate to very broadly cuneate, adaxially usually glabrous, abaxially usually thinly pubescent, sometimes densely so or glabrous. Inflorescence commonly of compounded cymes with up to 8 flowers.
</paragraph>
